{"id":"project-LICHEN-vx09","title":"edhoc_kdf CBOR encoding truncates length > 255 for TH and label","description":"File: rust/lichen-oscore/src/edhoc.rs
Lines: 130-146

The edhoc_kdf function encodes TH (transcript hash) and label as CBOR:
```rust
// TH as CBOR bstr
if th.len() <= 23 {
    info.push_err(0x40 | th.len() as u8)?;
} else {
    info.push_err(0x58)?;         // 1-byte length follows
    info.push_err(th.len() as u8)?;  // TRUNCATES if > 255
}
```

Similar issue for label at lines 140-146. The 0x58 prefix expects a 1-byte length, but if th.len() > 255, it truncates silently.

Currently TH is always 32 bytes (SHA-256 output) so not exploitable, but this is a latent bug.

Impact: Would produce malformed CBOR, causing key derivation mismatch with peers.

Fix: Add bounds check or use 0x59 (2-byte length) for values > 255.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:37:36.198905Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:37:36.198932Z"}

